In this op-ed, Vice President Joe Biden discusses the importance of delivering an accountable government that taxpayers deserve. He highlights the need to eliminate wasteful and non-essential expenses in government programs and discusses the Campaign to Cut Waste, which aims to ensure that tax dollars are used properly. Biden mentions the success of the Recovery Act Transparency Board in preventing fraud and waste, and announces the establishment of a new Government Accountability and Transparency Board. He also talks about the President's SAVE Award, where federal employees submit ideas to make government work more efficiently and save taxpayer money. Biden emphasizes the administration's efforts to make government more efficient, effective, and accountable, including changes in federal contracting, cracking down on improper payments, and selling off excess government real estate. He concludes by expressing the commitment to making tough decisions to address the federal deficit and providing the American people with the government they expect and deserve.